Field.Name: Account
Field.Description: Account mnemonic as agreed between buy and sell sides, e.g. broker and institution or investor/intermediary and fund manager.

Field.Name: AdvId
Field.Description: Unique identifier of advertisement message. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: AdvRefID
Field.Description: Reference identifier used with CANCEL and REPLACE transaction types. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: AdvSide
Field.Description: Broker's side of advertised trade

Field.Name: AdvTransType
Field.Description: Identifies advertisement message transaction type

Field.Name: AvgPx
Field.Description: Calculated average price of all fills on this order.

Field.Name: BeginSeqNo
Field.Description: Message sequence number of first message in range to be resent

Field.Name: BeginString
Field.Description: Identifies beginning of new message and protocol version. ALWAYS FIRST FIELD IN MESSAGE. (Always unencrypted)

Field.Name: BodyLength
Field.Description: Message length, in bytes, forward to the CheckSum field. ALWAYS SECOND FIELD IN MESSAGE. (Always unencrypted)

Field.Name: CheckSum
Field.Description: Three byte, simple checksum (see Volume 2: "Checksum Calculation" for description). ALWAYS LAST FIELD IN MESSAGE; i.e. serves, with the trailing <SOH>, as the end-of-message delimiter. Always defined as three characters. (Always unencrypted)

Field.Name: ClOrdID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for Order as assigned by the buy-side (institution, broker, intermediary etc.) (identified by SenderCompID or OnBehalfOfCompID as appropriate). Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day. Firms, particularly those which electronically submit multi-day orders, trade globally or throughout market close periods, should ensure uniqueness across days, for example by embedding a date within the ClOrdID field.

Field.Name: Commission
Field.Description: Commission. Note if CommType is percentage, Commission of 5% should be represented as .05.

Field.Name: CommType
Field.Description: Commission type

Field.Name: CumQty
Field.Description: Total quantity (e.g. number of shares) filled. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: Currency
Field.Description: Identifies currency used for price. Absence of this field is interpreted as the default for the security. It is recommended that systems provide the currency value whenever possible. See "Appendix 6-A: Valid Currency Codes" for information on obtaining valid values.

Field.Name: EndSeqNo
Field.Description: Message sequence number of last message in range to be resent. If request is for a single message BeginSeqNo = EndSeqNo. If request is for all messages subsequent to a particular message, EndSeqNo = "0" (representing infinity).

Field.Name: ExecID
Field.Description: Unique identifier of execution message as assigned by sell-side (broker, exchange, ECN) (will be 0 (zero) forExecType=I (Order Status)). Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day or the life of a multi-day order. Firms which accept multi-day orders should consider embedding a date within the ExecID field to assure uniqueness across days. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: ExecInst
Field.Description: (see Volume 1: "Glossary" for value definitions)

Field.Name: ExecRefID
Field.Description: Reference identifier used with Cancel and Correct transaction types. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: HandlInst
Field.Description: Instructions for order handling on Broker trading floor

Field.Name: SecurityIDSource
Field.Description: Identifies class or source of the SecurityID value. Required if SecurityID is specified. Values 100+ are reserved for private security identifications

Field.Name: IOIid
Field.Description: Unique identifier of IOI message. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: IOIQltyInd
Field.Description: Relative quality of indication

Field.Name: IOIRefID
Field.Description: Reference identifier used with CANCEL and REPLACE, transaction types. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: IOIQty
Field.Description: Quantity (e.g. number of shares) in numeric form or relative size.

Field.Name: IOITransType
Field.Description: Identifies IOI message transaction type

Field.Name: LastCapacity
Field.Description: Broker capacity in order execution

Field.Name: LastMkt
Field.Description: Market of execution for last fill Valid values: See "Appendix 6-C"

Field.Name: LastPx
Field.Description: Price of this (last) fill.

Field.Name: LastQty
Field.Description: Quantity (e.g. shares) bought/sold on this (last) fill. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: LinesOfText
Field.Description: Identifies number of lines of text body

Field.Name: MsgSeqNum
Field.Description: Integer message sequence number.

Field.Name: MsgType
Field.Description: Defines message type. ALWAYS THIRD FIELD IN MESSAGE. (Always unencrypted) Note: A "U" as the first character in the MsgType field (i.e. U1, U2, etc) indicates that the message format is privately defined between the sender and receiver.

Field.Name: NewSeqNo
Field.Description: New sequence number

Field.Name: OrderID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for Order as assigned by sell-side (broker, exchange, ECN). Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day. Firms which accept multi-day orders should consider embedding a date within the OrderID field to assure uniqueness across days.

Field.Name: OrderQty
Field.Description: Quantity ordered. This represents the number of shares for equities or based on normal convention the number of contracts for options, futures, convertible bonds, etc. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: OrdStatus
Field.Description: Identifies current status of order. *** SOME VALUES HAVE BEEN REPLACED - See "Replaced Features and Supported Approach" *** (see Volume 1: "Glossary" for value definitions)

Field.Name: OrdType
Field.Description: Order type. *** SOME VALUES HAVE BEEN DEPRECATED - See "Deprecated (Phased-out) Features and Supported Approach" *** (see Volume 1: "Glossary" for value definitions)

Field.Name: OrigClOrdID
Field.Description: ClOrdID of the previous order (NOT the initial order of the day) as assigned by the institution, used to identify the previous order in cancel and cancel/replace requests.

Field.Name: OrigTime
Field.Description: Time of message origination (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT"))

Field.Name: PossDupFlag
Field.Description: Indicates possible retransmission of message with this sequence number

Field.Name: Price
Field.Description: Price per unit of quantity (e.g. per share)

Field.Name: RefSeqNum
Field.Description: Reference message sequence number

Field.Name: Rule80A
Field.Description: *** DEPRECATED FIELD - See "Deprecated (Phased-out) Features and Supported Approach" *** Note that the name of this field is changing to "OrderCapacity" as Rule80A is a very US market-specific term. Other world markets need to convey similar information, however, often a subset of the US values. See the "Rule80A (aka OrderCapacity) Usage by Market" appendix for market-specific usage of this field.

Field.Name: SecurityID
Field.Description: Security identifier value of SecurityIDSource type (e.g. CUSIP, SEDOL, ISIN, etc). Requires SecurityIDSource.

Field.Name: SenderCompID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify firm sending message.

Field.Name: SenderSubID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator (desk, trader, etc.)

Field.Name: SendingTime
Field.Description: Time of message transmission (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

Field.Name: Quantity
Field.Description: Overall/total quantity (e.g. number of shares) (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: Side
Field.Description: Side of order

Field.Name: Symbol
Field.Description: Ticker symbol. Common, "human understood" representation of the security. SecurityID value can be specified if no symbol exists (e.g. non-exchange traded Collective Investment Vehicles)

Field.Name: TargetCompID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify receiving firm.

Field.Name: TargetSubID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific individual or unit intended to receive message. "ADMIN" reserved for administrative messages not intended for a specific user.

Field.Name: Text
Field.Description: Free format text string (Note: this field does not have a specified maximum length)

Field.Name: TimeInForce
Field.Description: Specifies how long the order remains in effect. Absence of this field is interpreted as DAY. NOTE not applicable to CIV Orders. (see Volume 1: "Glossary" for value definitions)

Field.Name: TransactTime
Field.Description: Time of execution/order creation (expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

Field.Name: Urgency
Field.Description: Urgency flag

Field.Name: ValidUntilTime
Field.Description: Indicates expiration time of indication message (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

Field.Name: SettlmntTyp
Field.Description: Indicates order settlement period. If present, FutSettDate (64) overrides this field. If both SettlmntTyp (63) and FutSettDate (64) are omitted, the default for SettlmntTyp (63) is 0 (Regular) Regular is defined as the default settlement period for the particular security on the exchange of execution.

Field.Name: FutSettDate
Field.Description: Specific date of trade settlement (SettlementDate) in YYYYMMDD format. If present, this field overrides SettlmntTyp (63). This field is required if the value of SettlmntTyp (63) is 6 (Future) or 8 (Sellers Option). This field must be omitted if the value of SettlmntTyp (63) is 7 (When and If Issued) (expressed in local time at place of settlement)

Field.Name: SymbolSfx
Field.Description: Additional information about the security (e.g. preferred, warrants, etc.). Note also see SecurityType (167). Valid values: As defined in the NYSE Stock and bond Symbol Directory and in the AMEX Fitch Directory

Field.Name: ListID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for list as assigned by institution, used to associate multiple individual orders. Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day. Firms which generate multi-day orders should consider embedding a date within the ListID field to assure uniqueness across days.

Field.Name: ListSeqNo
Field.Description: Sequence of individual order within list (i.e. ListSeqNo of TotNoOrds, 2 of 25, 3 of 25, . . . )

Field.Name: TotNoOrders
Field.Description: Total number of list order entries across all messages. Should be the sum of all NoOrders in each message that has repeating list order entries related to the same ListID. Used to support fragmentation. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was named "ListNoOrds")

Field.Name: ListExecInst
Field.Description: Free format text message containing list handling and execution instructions.

Field.Name: AllocID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for allocation message. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: AllocTransType
Field.Description: Identifies allocation transaction type *** SOME VALUES HAVE BEEN REPLACED - See "Replaced Features and Supported Approach" ***

Field.Name: RefAllocID
Field.Description: Reference identifier to be used with AllocTransType=Replace or Cancel or with AllocType = "Sellside Calculated Using Preliminary". (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: NoOrders
Field.Description: Indicates number of orders to be combined for average pricing and allocation.

Field.Name: AvgPrxPrecision
Field.Description: Indicates number of decimal places to be used for average pricing. Absence of this field indicates that default precision arranged by the broker/institution is to be used.

Field.Name: TradeDate
Field.Description: Indicates date of trade referenced in this message in YYYYMMDD format. Absence of this field indicates current day (expressed in local time at place of trade).

Field.Name: PositionEffect
Field.Description: Indicates whether the resulting position after a trade should be an opening position or closing position. Used for omnibus accounting - where accounts are held on a gross basis instead of being netted together.

Field.Name: NoAllocs
Field.Description: Number of repeating AllocAccount/AllocPrice entries.

Field.Name: AllocAccount
Field.Description: Sub-account mnemonic

Field.Name: AllocQty
Field.Description: Quantity to be allocated to specific sub-account (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: ProcessCode
Field.Description: Processing code for sub-account. Absence of this field in AllocAccount / AllocPrice/AllocQty / ProcessCode instance indicates regular trade.

Field.Name: NoRpts
Field.Description: Total number of reports within series.

Field.Name: RptSeq
Field.Description: Sequence number of message within report series.

Field.Name: CxlQty
Field.Description: Total quantity canceled for this order. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: AllocStatus
Field.Description: Identifies status of allocation.

Field.Name: AllocRejCode
Field.Description: Identifies reason for rejection.

Field.Name: Signature
Field.Description: Electronic signature

Field.Name: SecureDataLen
Field.Description: Length of encrypted message

Field.Name: SecureData
Field.Description: Actual encrypted data stream

Field.Name: SignatureLength
Field.Description: Number of bytes in signature field.

Field.Name: EmailType
Field.Description: Email message type.

Field.Name: RawDataLength
Field.Description: Number of bytes in raw data field.

Field.Name: RawData
Field.Description: Unformatted raw data, can include bitmaps, word processor documents, etc.

Field.Name: PossResend
Field.Description: Indicates that message may contain information that has been sent under another sequence number.

Field.Name: EncryptMethod
Field.Description: Method of encryption.

Field.Name: StopPx
Field.Description: Price per unit of quantity (e.g. per share)

Field.Name: ExDestination
Field.Description: Execution destination as defined by institution when order is entered. Valid values: See "Appendix 6-C"

Field.Name: CxlRejReason
Field.Description: Code to identify reason for cancel rejection.

Field.Name: OrdRejReason
Field.Description: Code to identify reason for order rejection.

Field.Name: IOIQualifier
Field.Description: Code to qualify IOI use.

Field.Name: Issuer
Field.Description: Company name of security issuer (e.g. International Business Machines) see also Volume 7: "PRODUCT: FIXED INCOME - Euro Soverign Issuer Codes"

Field.Name: SecurityDesc
Field.Description: Security description.

Field.Name: HeartBtInt
Field.Description: Heartbeat interval (seconds)

Field.Name: MinQty
Field.Description: Minimum quantity of an order to be executed. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: MaxFloor
Field.Description: Maximum quantity (e.g. number of shares) within an order to be shown on the exchange floor at any given time. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: TestReqID
Field.Description: Identifier included in Test Request message to be returned in resulting Heartbeat

Field.Name: ReportToExch
Field.Description: Identifies party of trade responsible for exchange reporting.

Field.Name: LocateReqd
Field.Description: Indicates whether the broker is to locate the stock in conjunction with a short sell order.

Field.Name: OnBehalfOfCompID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify firm originating message if the message was delivered by a third party i.e. the third party firm identifier would be delivered in the SenderCompID field and the firm originating the message in this field.

Field.Name: OnBehalfOfSubID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator (i.e. trader) if the message was delivered by a third party

Field.Name: QuoteID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for quote

Field.Name: NetMoney
Field.Description: Total amount due as the result of the transaction (e.g. for Buy order - principal + commission + fees) reported in currency of execution.

Field.Name: SettlCurrAmt
Field.Description: Total amount due expressed in settlement currency (includes the effect of the forex transaction)

Field.Name: SettlCurrency
Field.Description: Currency code of settlement denomination.

Field.Name: ForexReq
Field.Description: Indicates request for forex accommodation trade to be executed along with security transaction.

Field.Name: OrigSendingTime
Field.Description: Original time of message transmission (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT") when transmitting orders as the result of a resend request.

Field.Name: GapFillFlag
Field.Description: Indicates that the Sequence Reset message is replacing administrative or application messages which will not be resent.

Field.Name: NoExecs
Field.Description: No of execution repeating group entries to follow.

Field.Name: ExpireTime
Field.Description: Time/Date of order expiration (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

Field.Name: DKReason
Field.Description: Reason for execution rejection.

Field.Name: DeliverToCompID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify the firm targeted to receive the message if the message is delivered by a third party i.e. the third party firm identifier would be delivered in the TargetCompID field and the ultimate receiver firm ID in this field.

Field.Name: DeliverToSubID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific message recipient (i.e. trader) if the message is delivered by a third party

Field.Name: IOINaturalFlag
Field.Description: Indicates that IOI is the result of an existing agency order or a facilitation position resulting from an agency order, not from principal trading or order solicitation activity.

Field.Name: QuoteReqID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for quote request

Field.Name: BidPx
Field.Description: Bid price/rate

Field.Name: OfferPx
Field.Description: Offer price/rate

Field.Name: BidSize
Field.Description: Quantity of bid (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: OfferSize
Field.Description: Quantity of offer (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: NoMiscFees
Field.Description: Number of repeating groups of miscellaneous fees

Field.Name: MiscFeeAmt
Field.Description: Miscellaneous fee value

Field.Name: MiscFeeCurr
Field.Description: Currency of miscellaneous fee

Field.Name: MiscFeeType
Field.Description: Indicates type of miscellaneous fee.

Field.Name: PrevClosePx
Field.Description: Previous closing price of security.

Field.Name: ResetSeqNumFlag
Field.Description: Indicates that the both sides of the FIX session should reset sequence numbers.

Field.Name: SenderLocationID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator’s location (i.e. geographic location and/or desk, trader)

Field.Name: TargetLocationID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific message destination’s location (i.e. geographic location and/or desk, trader)

Field.Name: OnBehalfOfLocationID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator’s location (i.e. geographic location and/or desk, trader) if the message was delivered by a third party

Field.Name: DeliverToLocationID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific message recipient’s location (i.e. geographic location and/or desk, trader) if the message was delivered by a third party

Field.Name: NoRelatedSym
Field.Description: Specifies the number of repeating symbols specified.

Field.Name: Subject
Field.Description: The subject of an Email message

Field.Name: Headline
Field.Description: The headline of a News message

Field.Name: URLLink
Field.Description: A URL (Uniform Resource Locator) link to additional information (i.e. http://www.XYZ.com/research.html)

Field.Name: ExecType
Field.Description: Describes the specific ExecutionRpt (i.e. Pending Cancel) while OrdStatus will always identify the current order status (i.e. Partially Filled) *** SOME VALUES HAVE BEEN REPLACED - See "Replaced Features and Supported Approach" ***

Field.Name: LeavesQty
Field.Description: Quantity open for further execution. If the OrdStatus is Canceled, DoneForTheDay, Expired, Calculated, or Rejected (in which case the order is no longer active) then LeavesQty could be 0, otherwise LeavesQty = OrderQty - CumQty. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: CashOrderQty
Field.Description: Specifies the approximate order quantity desired in total monetary units vs. as tradeable units (e.g. number of shares). The broker or fund manager (for CIV orders) would be responsible for converting and calculating a tradeable unit (e.g. share) quantity (OrderQty) based upon this amount to be used for the actual order and subsequent messages.

Field.Name: AllocAvgPx
Field.Description: AvgPx for a specific AllocAccount

Field.Name: AllocNetMoney
Field.Description: NetMoney for a specific AllocAccount

Field.Name: SettlCurrFxRate
Field.Description: Foreign exchange rate used to compute SettlCurrAmt from Currency to SettlCurrency

Field.Name: SettlCurrFxRateCalc
Field.Description: Specifies whether or not SettlCurrFxRate should be multiplied or divided.

Field.Name: NumDaysInterest
Field.Description: Number of Days of Interest for convertible bonds and fixed income. Note value may be negative.

Field.Name: AccruedInterestRate
Field.Description: Accrued Interest Rate for convertible bonds and fixed income

Field.Name: AccruedInterestAmt
Field.Description: Amount of Accrued Interest for convertible bonds and fixed income

Field.Name: SettlInstMode
Field.Description: Indicates mode used for Settlement Instructions

Field.Name: AllocText
Field.Description: Free format text related to a specific AllocAccount.

Field.Name: SettlInstID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for Settlement Instructions message.

Field.Name: SettlInstTransType
Field.Description: Settlement Instructions message transaction type

Field.Name: EmailThreadID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for an email thread (new and chain of replies)

Field.Name: SettlInstSource
Field.Description: Indicates source of Settlement Instructions

Field.Name: SecurityType
Field.Description: Indicates type of security. See also the Product and CFICode fields. It is recommended that CFICode be used instead of SecurityType for non-Fixed Income instruments.

Field.Name: EffectiveTime
Field.Description: Time the details within the message should take effect (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

Field.Name: StandInstDbType
Field.Description: Identifies the Standing Instruction database used

Field.Name: StandInstDbName
Field.Description: Name of the Standing Instruction database represented with StandInstDbType (i.e. the Global Custodian’s name).

Field.Name: StandInstDbID
Field.Description: Unique identifier used on the Standing Instructions database for the Standing Instructions to be referenced.

Field.Name: SettlDeliveryType
Field.Description: Identifies type of settlement

Field.Name: SettlDepositoryCode
Field.Description: Broker’s account code at the depository (i.e. CEDEL ID for CEDEL, FINS for DTC, or Euroclear ID for Euroclear) if SettlLocation is a depository

Field.Name: SettlBrkrCode
Field.Description: BIC (Bank Identification Code—Swift managed) code of the broker involved (i.e. for multi-company brokerage firms)

Field.Name: SettlInstCode
Field.Description: BIC (Bank Identification Code—Swift managed) code of the institution involved (i.e. for multi-company institution firms)

Field.Name: SecuritySettlAgentName
Field.Description: Name of SettlInstSource's local agent bank if SettlLocation is not a depository

Field.Name: SecuritySettlAgentCode
Field.Description: BIC (Bank Identification Code--Swift managed) code of the SettlInstSource's local agent bank if SettlLocation is not a depository

Field.Name: SecuritySettlAgentAcctNum
Field.Description: SettlInstSource's account number at local agent bank if SettlLocation is not a depository

Field.Name: SecuritySettlAgentAcctName
Field.Description: Name of SettlInstSource's account at local agent bank if SettlLocation is not a depository

Field.Name: SecuritySettlAgentContactName
Field.Description: Name of contact at local agent bank for SettlInstSource's account if SettlLocation is not a depository

Field.Name: SecuritySettlAgentContactPhone
Field.Description: Phone number for contact at local agent bank if SettlLocation is not a depository

Field.Name: CashSettlAgentName
Field.Description: Name of SettlInstSource's local agent bank if SettlDeliveryType=Free

Field.Name: CashSettlAgentCode
Field.Description: BIC (Bank Identification Code--Swift managed) code of the SettlInstSource's local agent bank if SettlDeliveryType=Free

Field.Name: CashSettlAgentAcctNum
Field.Description: SettlInstSource's account number at local agent bank if SettlDeliveryType=Free

Field.Name: CashSettlAgentAcctName
Field.Description: Name of SettlInstSource's account at local agent bank if SettlDeliveryType=Free

Field.Name: CashSettlAgentContactName
Field.Description: Name of contact at local agent bank for SettlInstSource's account if SettlDeliveryType=Free

Field.Name: CashSettlAgentContactPhone
Field.Description: Phone number for contact at local agent bank for SettlInstSource's account if SettlDeliveryType=Free

Field.Name: BidSpotRate
Field.Description: Bid F/X spot rate.

Field.Name: BidForwardPoints
Field.Description: Bid F/X forward points added to spot rate. May be a negative value.

Field.Name: OfferSpotRate
Field.Description: Offer F/X spot rate.

Field.Name: OfferForwardPoints
Field.Description: Offer F/X forward points added to spot rate. May be a negative value.

Field.Name: OrderQty2
Field.Description: OrderQty of the future part of a F/X swap order.

Field.Name: FutSettDate2
Field.Description: FutSettDate of the future part of a F/X swap order.

Field.Name: LastSpotRate
Field.Description: F/X spot rate.

Field.Name: LastForwardPoints
Field.Description: F/X forward points added to LastSpotRate. May be a negative value.

Field.Name: AllocLinkID
Field.Description: Can be used to link two different Allocation messages (each with unique AllocID) together, i.e. for F/X "Netting" or "Swaps". Should be unique.

Field.Name: AllocLinkType
Field.Description: Identifies the type of Allocation linkage when AllocLinkID is used.

Field.Name: SecondaryOrderID
Field.Description: Assigned by the party which accepts the order. Can be used to provide the OrderID used by an exchange or executing system.

Field.Name: NoIOIQualifiers
Field.Description: Number of repeating groups of IOIQualifiers.

Field.Name: MaturityMonthYear
Field.Description: Can be used with standardized derivatives vs. the MaturityDate field. Month and Year of the maturity (used for standardized futures and options). Format: YYYYMM (i.e. 199903)

Field.Name: StrikePrice
Field.Description: Strike Price for an Option.

Field.Name: CoveredOrUncovered
Field.Description: Used for derivative products, such as options

Field.Name: OptAttribute
Field.Description: Can be used for SecurityType=OPT to identify a particular security.

Field.Name: SecurityExchange
Field.Description: Market used to help identify a security. Valid values: See "Appendix 6-C"

Field.Name: NotifyBrokerOfCredit
Field.Description: Indicates whether or not details should be communicated to BrokerOfCredit (i.e. step-in broker).

Field.Name: AllocHandlInst
Field.Description: Indicates how the receiver (i.e. third party) of Allocation message should handle/process the account details.

Field.Name: MaxShow
Field.Description: Maximum quantity (e.g. number of shares) within an order to be shown to other customers (i.e. sent via an IOI). (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: PegDifference
Field.Description: Amount (signed) added to the price of the peg for a pegged order.

Field.Name: XmlDataLen
Field.Description: Length of the XmlData data block.

Field.Name: XmlData
Field.Description: Actual XML data stream (e.g. FIXML). See approriate XML reference (e.g. FIXML). Note: may contain embedded SOH characters.

Field.Name: SettlInstRefID
Field.Description: Reference identifier for the SettlInstID with Cancel and Replace SettlInstTransType transaction types.

Field.Name: NoRoutingIDs
Field.Description: Number of repeating groups of RoutingID and RoutingType values. See Volume 3: "Pre-Trade Message Targeting/Routing"

Field.Name: RoutingType
Field.Description: Indicates the type of RoutingID specified.

Field.Name: RoutingID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify a specific routing destination.

Field.Name: Spread
Field.Description: For Fixed Income. Either Swap Spread or Spread to Benchmark depending upon the order type. Spread to Benchmark: Basis points relative to a benchmark. To be expressed as "count of basis points" (vs. an absolute value). E.g. High Grade Corporate Bonds may express price as basis points relative to benchmark (the Benchmark field). Note: Basis points can be negative. Swap Spread: Target spread for a swap.

Field.Name: Benchmark
Field.Description: *** DEPRECATED FIELD - See "Deprecated (Phased-out) Features and Supported Approach" *** For Fixed Income. Identifies the benchmark (e.g. used in conjunction with the Spread field).

Field.Name: BenchmarkCurveCurrency
Field.Description: Identifies currency used for benchmark curve. See "Appendix 6-A: Valid Currency Codes" for information on obtaining valid values. (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

Field.Name: BenchmarkCurveName
Field.Description: Name of benchmark curve.

Field.Name: BenchmarkCurvePoint
Field.Description: Point on benchmark curve. Free form values: e.g. "1Y", "7Y", "INTERPOLATED". Sample values: 1M = combination of a number between 1-12 and a "M" for month 1Y = combination of number between 1-100 and a "Y" for year} 10Y-OLD = see above, then add "-OLD" when appropriate INTERPOLATED = the point is mathematically derived 2/2031 5 3/8 = the point is stated via a combination of maturity month / year and coupon See Fixed Income-specific documentation at http://www.fixprotocol.org for additional values. (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

Field.Name: CouponRate
Field.Description: For Fixed Income. Coupon rate of the bond. Will be zero for step-up bonds.

Field.Name: CouponPaymentDate

See "Appendix 6-G – Use of <Parties> Component Block" Valid values: Applicable to all PartyRoles unless otherwise specified: B = BIC (Bank Identification Code—Swift managed) code (ISO 9362 - See "Appendix 6-B") C = Generally accepted market participant identifier (e.g. NASD mnemonic) D = Proprietary/Custom code E = ISO Country Code F = Settlement Entity Location (note if Local Market Settlement use "E = ISO Country Code") (see "Appendix 6-G" for valid values) For PartyRole="Investor ID" and for Equities: 1 = Korean Investor ID 2 = Taiwanese Qualified Foreign Investor ID QFII / FID 3 = Taiwanese Trading Account 4 = Malaysian Central Depository (MCD) number 5 = Chinese B Share (Shezhen and Shanghai) See Volume 4: "Example Usage of PartyRole="Investor ID" " For PartyRole="Investor ID" and for CIV: 6 = UK National Insurance or Pension Number 7 = US Social Security Number 8 = US Employer Identification Number 9 = Australian Business Number A = Australian Tax File Number

Field.Name: PartyID
Field.Description: Party identifier/code. See PartyIDSource (447) and PartyRole (452). See "Appendix 6-G – Use of <Parties> Component Block"

Field.Name: TotalVolumeTradedDate
Field.Description: Date of TotalVolumeTraded.

Field.Name: TotalVolumeTradedTime
Field.Description: Time of TotalVolumeTraded.

Field.Name: NetChgPrevDay
Field.Description: Net change from previous day’s closing price vs. last traded price.

Field.Name: PartyRole
Field.Description: Identifies the type or role of the PartyID specified. See "Appendix 6-G – Use of <Parties> Component Block"

Field.Name: NoPartyIDs
Field.Description: Number of PartyID, PartyIDSource, and PartyRole entries

Field.Name: NoSecurityAltID
Field.Description: Number of SecurityAltID entries.

Field.Name: SecurityAltID
Field.Description: Alternate Security identifier value for this security of SecurityAltIDSource type (e.g. CUSIP, SEDOL, ISIN, etc). Requires SecurityAltIDSource.

Field.Name: SecurityAltIDSource
Field.Description: Identifies class or source of the SecurityAltID value. Required if SecurityAltID is specified. Valid values: Same valid values as the SecurityIDSource field

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingSecurityAltID
Field.Description: Number of UnderlyingSecurityAltID entries.

Field.Name: UnderlyingSecurityAltID
Field.Description: Alternate Security identifier value for this underlying security of UnderlyingSecurityAltIDSource type (e.g. CUSIP, SEDOL, ISIN, etc). Requires UnderlyingSecurityAltIDSource.

Field.Name: UnderlyingSecurityAltIDSource
Field.Description: Identifies class or source of the UnderlyingSecurityAltID value. Required if UnderlyingSecurityAltID is specified. Valid values: Same valid values as the SecurityIDSource (22) field

Field.Name: Product
Field.Description: Indicates the type of product the security is associated with. See also the CFICode (461) and SecurityType (167) fields.

Field.Name: CFICode
Field.Description: Indicates the type of security using ISO 10962 standard, Classification of Financial Instruments (CFI code) values. ISO 10962 is maintained by ANNA (Association of National Numbering Agencies) acting as Registration Authority. See "Appendix 6-B FIX Fields Based Upon Other Standards". See also the Product (460) and SecurityType (167) fields. It is recommended that CFICode be used instead of SecurityType (167) for non-Fixed Income instruments. A subset of possible values applicable to FIX usage are identified in "Appendix 6-D CFICode Usage - ISO 10962 Classification of Financial Instruments (CFI code)"

Field.Name: UnderlyingProduct
Field.Description: Underlying security’s Product. Valid values: see Product(460) field

Field.Name: UnderlyingCFICode
Field.Description: Underlying security’s CFICode. Valid values: see CFICode (461)field

Field.Name: TestMessageIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether or not this FIX Session is a "test" vs. "production" connection. Useful for preventing "accidents".

Field.Name: QuantityType
Field.Description: Designates the type of quantities (e.g. OrderQty) specified. Used for MBS and TIPS Fixed Income security types.

Field.Name: BookingRefID
Field.Description: Common reference passed to a post-trade booking process (e.g. industry matching utility).

Field.Name: IndividualAllocID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for a specific NoAllocs repeating group instance (e.g. for an AllocAccount).

Field.Name: RoundingDirection
Field.Description: Specifies which direction to round For CIV – indicates whether or not the quantity of shares/units is to be rounded and in which direction where OrderCashAmt or (for CIV only) OrderPercent are specified on an order. The default is for rounding to be at the discretion of the executing broker or fund manager. e.g. for an order specifying CashOrdQty or OrderPercent if the calculated number of shares/units was 325.76 and RoundingModulus was 10 – "round down" would give 320 units, "round up" would give 330 units and "round to nearest" would give 320 units.

Field.Name: RoundingModulus
Field.Description: For CIV - a float value indicating the value to which rounding is required. i.e. 10 means round to a multiple of 10 units/shares; 0.5 means round to a multiple of 0.5 units/shares. The default, if RoundingDirection is specified without RoundingModulus, is to round to a whole unit/share.

Field.Name: CountryOfIssue
Field.Description: ISO Country code of instrument issue (e.g. the country portion typically used in ISIN). Can be used in conjunction with non-ISIN SecurityID (e.g. CUSIP for Municipal Bonds without ISIN) to provide uniqueness.

Field.Name: StateOrProvinceOfIssue
Field.Description: A two-character state or province abbreviation.

Field.Name: LocaleOfIssue
Field.Description: Identifies the locale. For Municipal Security Issuers other than state or province. Refer to http://www.atmos.albany.edu/cgi/stagrep-cgi Reference the IATA city codes for values. Note IATA (International Air Transport Association) maintains the codes at www.iata.org. See "Volume 7 – PRODUCT: FIXED INCOME" for example.

Field.Name: NoRegistDtls
Field.Description: The number of registration details on a Registration Instructions message

Field.Name: MailingDtls
Field.Description: Set of Correspondence address details, possibly including phone, fax, etc.

Field.Name: InvestorCountryOfResidence
Field.Description: The ISO 3166 Country code (2 character) identifying which country the beneficial investor is resident for tax purposes.

Field.Name: PaymentRef
Field.Description: "Settlement Payment Reference" – A free format Payment reference to assist with reconciliation, e.g. a Client and/or Order ID number.

Field.Name: DistribPaymentMethod
Field.Description: A code identifying the payment method for a (fractional) distribution. 1 = CREST 2 = NSCC 3 = Euroclear 4 = Clearstream 5 = Cheque 6 = Telegraphic Transfer 7 = FedWire 8 = Direct Credit (BECS, BACS) 9 = ACH Credit 10 = BPAY 11 = High Value Clearing System (HVACS) 12 = Reinvest in fund 13 through 998 are reserved for future use Values above 1000 are available for use by private agreement among counterparties

Field.Name: CashDistribCurr
Field.Description: Specifies currency to be use for Cash Distributions– see "Appendix 6-A; Valid Currency Codes".

Field.Name: CommCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies currency to be use for Commission if the Commission currency is different from the Deal Currency - see "Appendix 6-A; Valid Currency Codes".

Field.Name: CancellationRights
Field.Description: For CIV – A one character code identifying whether Cancellation rights/Cooling off period applies.

Field.Name: MoneyLaunderingStatus
Field.Description: For CIV - A one character code identifying Money laundering status.

Field.Name: MailingInst
Field.Description: Free format text to specify mailing instruction requirements, e.g. "no third party mailings".

Field.Name: TransBkdTime
Field.Description: For CIV A date and time stamp to indicate the time a CIV order was booked by the fund manager.

Field.Name: ExecPriceType
Field.Description: For CIV - Identifies how the execution price LastPx was calculated from the fund unit/share price(s) calculated at the fund valuation point.

Field.Name: ExecPriceAdjustment
Field.Description: For CIV the amount or percentage by which the fund unit/share price was adjusted, as indicated by ExecPriceType

Field.Name: DateOfBirth
Field.Description: The date of birth applicable to the individual, e.g. required to open some types of tax-exempt account.

Field.Name: TradeReportTransType
Field.Description: Identifies Trade Report message transaction type

Field.Name: CardHolderName
Field.Description: The name of the payment card holder as specified on the card being used for payment.

Field.Name: CardNumber
Field.Description: The number of the payment card as specified on the card being used for payment.

Field.Name: CardExpDate
Field.Description: The expiry date of the payment card as specified on the card being used for payment.

Field.Name: CardIssNo
Field.Description: The issue number of the payment card as specified on the card being used for payment. This is only applicable to certain types of card.

Field.Name: PaymentMethod
Field.Description: A code identifying the Settlement payment method. 1 = CREST 2 = NSCC 3 = Euroclear 4 = Clearstream 5 = Cheque 6 = Telegraphic Transfer 7 = FedWire 8 = Debit Card 9 = Direct Debit (BECS) 10 = Direct Credit (BECS) 11 = Credit Card 12 = ACH Debit 13 = ACH Credit 14 = BPAY 15 = High Value Clearing System (HVACS) 16 through 998 are reserved for future use Values above 1000 are available for use by private agreement among counterparties

Field.Name: RegistAcctType
Field.Description: For CIV – a fund manager-defined code identifying which of the fund manager’s account types is required.

Field.Name: Designation
Field.Description: Free format text defining the designation to be associated with a holding on the register. Used to identify assets of a specific underlying investor using a common registration, e.g. a broker’s nominee or street name.

Field.Name: TaxAdvantageType
Field.Description: For CIV - a code identifying the type of tax exempt account in which purchased shares/units are to be held. 0=None/Not Applicable (default) 1 = Maxi ISA (UK) 2 = TESSA (UK) 3 = Mini Cash ISA (UK) 4 = Mini Stocks and Shares ISA (UK) 5 = Mini Insurance ISA (UK) 6 = Current year payment (US) 7 = Prior year payment (US) 8 = Asset transfer (US) 9 = Employee - prior year (US) 10 = Employee – current year (US) 11 = Employer - prior year (US) 12 = Employer – current year (US) 13 = Non-fund prototype IRA (US) 14 = Non-fund qualified plan (US) 15 = Defined contribution plan (US) 16 = Individual Retirement Account (US) 17 = Individual Retirement Account – Rollover (US) 18 = KEOGH (US) 19 = Profit Sharing Plan (US) 20 = 401K (US) 21 = Self-Directed IRA (US) 22 = 403(b) (US) 23 = 457 (US) 24 = Roth IRA (fund prototype) (US) 25 = Roth IRA (non-prototype) (US) 26 = Roth Conversion IRA (fund prototype) (US) 27 = Roth Conversion IRA (non-prototype) (US) 28 = Education IRA (fund prototype) (US) 29 = Education IRA (non-prototype) (US) 30 – 998 are reserved for future use by recognized taxation authorities 999=Other values above 1000 are available for use by private agreement among counterparties

Field.Name: RegistRejReasonText
Field.Description: Text indicating reason(s) why a Registration Instruction has been rejected.

Field.Name: FundRenewWaiv
Field.Description: A one character code identifying whether the Fund based renewal commission is to be waived.

Field.Name: CashDistribAgentName
Field.Description: Name of local agent bank if for cash distributions

Field.Name: CashDistribAgentCode
Field.Description: BIC (Bank Identification Code--Swift managed) code of agent bank for cash distributions

Field.Name: CashDistribAgentAcctNumber
Field.Description: Account number at agent bank for distributions.

Field.Name: CashDistribPayRef
Field.Description: Free format Payment reference to assist with reconciliation of distributions.

Field.Name: CardStartDate
Field.Description: The start date of the card as specified on the card being used for payment.

Field.Name: PaymentDate
Field.Description: The date written on a cheque or date payment should be submitted to the relevant clearing system.

Field.Name: PaymentRemitterID
Field.Description: Identifies sender of a payment, e.g. the payment remitter or a customer reference number.

Field.Name: RegistStatus
Field.Description: Registration status as returned by the broker or (for CIV) the fund manager

Field.Name: RegistRejReasonCode
Field.Description: Reason(s) why Registration Instructions has been rejected. The reason may be further amplified in the RegistRejReasonCode field.

Field.Name: RegistRefID
Field.Description: Reference identifier for the RegistID with Cancel and Replace RegistTransType transaction types.

Field.Name: RegistDetls
Field.Description: Set of Registration name and address details, possibly including phone, fax etc.

Field.Name: NoDistribInsts
Field.Description: The number of Distribution Instructions on a Registration Instructions message

Field.Name: RegistEmail
Field.Description: Email address relating to Registration name and address details

Field.Name: DistribPercentage
Field.Description: The amount of each distribution to go to this beneficiary, expressed as a percentage

Field.Name: RegistID
Field.Description: Unique identifier of the registration details as assigned by institution or intermediary.

Field.Name: RegistTransType
Field.Description: Identifies Registration Instructions transaction type Valid values: 0 = New 1 = Replace 2 = Cancel

Field.Name: ExecValuationPoint
Field.Description: For CIV - a date and time stamp to indicate the fund valuation point with respect to which a order was priced by the fund manager.

Field.Name: OrderPercent
Field.Description: For CIV specifies the approximate order quantity desired. For a CIV Sale it specifies percentage of investor’s total holding to be sold. For a CIV switch/exchange it specifies percentage of investor’s cash realised from sales to be re-invested. The executing broker, intermediary or fund manager is responsible for converting and calculating OrderQty in shares/units for subsequent messages.

Field.Name: OwnershipType
Field.Description: The relationship between Registration parties.

Field.Name: NoContAmts
Field.Description: The number of Contract Amount details on an Execution Report message

Field.Name: ContAmtType
Field.Description: Type of Contract Amount. For UK valid values include: 1 = Commission Amount (actual) 2 = Commission % (actual) 3 = Initial Charge Amount 4 = Initial Charge % 5 = Discount Amount 6 = Discount % 7 = Dilution Levy Amount 8 = Dilution Levy % 9 = Exit Charge Amount 10 = Exit Charge % 11 = Fund-based Renewal Commission % (a.k.a. Trail commission) 12 = Projected Fund Value (i.e. for investments intended to realise or exceed a specific future value) 13 = Fund-based Renewal Commission Amount (based on Order value) 14 = Fund-based Renewal Commission Amount (based on Projected Fund value) 15 = Net Settlement Amount NOTE That Commission Amount / % in Contract Amounts is the commission actually charged, rather than the commission instructions given in Fields 12/13.

Field.Name: ContAmtValue
Field.Description: Value of Contract Amount, e.g. a financial amount or percentage as indicated by ContAmtType.

Field.Name: ContAmtCurr
Field.Description: Specifies currency for the Contract amount if different from the Deal Currency - see "Appendix A; Valid Currency Codes".

Field.Name: OwnerType
Field.Description: Identifies the type of owner.

Field.Name: PartySubID
Field.Description: Sub-identifier (e.g. Clearing Account for PartyRole=Clearing Firm, Locate ID # for PartyRole=Locate/Lending Firm, etc). Not required when using PartyID, PartyIDSource, and PartyRole.

Field.Name: NestedPartyID
Field.Description: PartyID value within a nested repeating group. Same values as PartyID (448)

Field.Name: NestedPartyIDSource
Field.Description: PartyIDSource value within a nested repeating group. Same values as PartyIDSource (447)

Field.Name: SecondaryClOrdID
Field.Description: Assigned by the party which originates the order. Can be used to provide the ClOrdID used by an exchange or executing system.

Field.Name: SecondaryExecID
Field.Description: Assigned by the party which accepts the order. Can be used to provide the ExecID used by an exchange or executing system.

Field.Name: OrderCapacity
Field.Description: Designates the capacity of the firm placing the order. (as of FIX 4.3, this field replaced Rule80A (tag 47) --used in conjunction with OrderRestrictions field)

Field.Name: OrderRestrictions
Field.Description: Restrictions associated with an order. If more than one restriction is applicable to an order, this field can contain multiple instructions separated by space.

Field.Name: MassCancelRequestType
Field.Description: Specifies scope of Order Mass Cancel Request.

Field.Name: MassCancelResponse
Field.Description: Specifies the action taken by counterparty order handling system as a result of the Order Mass Cancel Request

Field.Name: MassCancelRejectReason
Field.Description: Reason Order Mass Cancel Request was rejected

Field.Name: TotalAffectedOrders
Field.Description: Total number of orders affected by mass cancel request.

Field.Name: NoAffectedOrders
Field.Description: Number of affected orders in the repeating group of order ids.

Field.Name: AffectedOrderID
Field.Description: OrderID of an order affected by a mass cancel request.

Field.Name: AffectedSecondaryOrderID
Field.Description: SecondaryOrderID of an order affected by a mass cancel request.

Field.Name: QuoteType
Field.Description: Identifies the type of quote. Valid values: 0 = Indicative 1 = Tradeable 2 = Restricted Tradeable An indicative quote is used to inform a counterparty of a market. An indicative quote does not result directly in a trade. A tradeable quote is submitted to a market and willresult directly in a trade against other orders and quotes in a market. A restricted tradeable quote is submitted to a market and within a certain restriction (possibly based upon price or quantity) will automatically trade against orders. Order that do not comply with restrictions are sent to the quote issuer who can choose to accept or decline the order.

Field.Name: NestedPartyRole
Field.Description: PartyRole value within a nested repeating group. Same values as PartyRole (452)

Field.Name: NoNestedPartyIDs
Field.Description: Number of NestedPartyID, NestedPartyIDSource, and NestedPartyRole entries

Field.Name: TotalAccruedInterestAmt
Field.Description: Total Amount of Accrued Interest for convertible bonds and fixed income

Field.Name: MaturityDate
Field.Description: Date of maturity.

Field.Name: UnderlyingMaturityDate
Field.Description: Underlying security’s maturity date. See MaturityDate (541) field for description

Field.Name: InstrRegistry
Field.Description: The location at which records of ownership are maintained for this instrument, and at which ownership changes must be recorded.

Field.Name: CashMargin
Field.Description: Identifies whether an order is a margin order or a non-margin order. This is primarily used when sending orders to Japanese exchanges to indicate sell margin or buy to cover. The same tag could be assigned also by buy-side to indicate the intent to sell or buy margin and the sell-side to accept or reject (base on some validation criteria) the margin request.

Field.Name: NestedPartySubID
Field.Description: PartySubID value within a nested repeating group. Same values as PartySubID (523)

Field.Name: Scope
Field.Description: Defines the scope of a data element.

Field.Name: MDImplicitDelete
Field.Description: Defines how a server handles distribution of a truncated book. Defaults to broker option.

Field.Name: CrossID
Field.Description: Identifier for a cross order. Must be unique during a given trading day. Recommend that firms use the order date as part of the CrossID for Good Till Cancel (GT) orders.

Field.Name: CrossType
Field.Description: Type of cross being submitted to a market

Field.Name: CrossPrioritization
Field.Description: Indicates if one side or the other of a cross order should be prioritized. 0 = None 1 = Buy side is prioritized 2 = Sell side is prioritized The definition of prioritization is left to the market. In some markets prioritization means which side of the cross order is applied to the market first. In other markets – prioritization may mean that the prioritized side is fully executed (sometimes referred to as the side being protected).

Field.Name: OrigCrossID
Field.Description: CrossID of the previous cross order (NOT the initial cross order of the day) as assigned by the institution, used to identify the previous cross order in Cross Cancel and Cross Cancel/Replace Requests.

Field.Name: NoSides
Field.Description: Number of Side repeating group instances.

Field.Name: Username
Field.Description: Userid or username.

Field.Name: Password
Field.Description: Password or passphrase.

Field.Name: NoLegs
Field.Description: Number of InstrumentLeg repeating group instances.

Field.Name: LegCurrency
Field.Description: Currency associated with a particular Leg's quantity

Field.Name: TotalNumSecurityTypes
Field.Description: Indicates total number of security types in the event that multiple Security Type messages are used to return results

Field.Name: NoSecurityTypes
Field.Description: Number of Security Type repeating group instances.

Field.Name: SecurityListRequestType
Field.Description: Identifies the type/criteria of Security List Request

Field.Name: SecurityRequestResult
Field.Description: The results returned to a Security Request message

Field.Name: RoundLot
Field.Description: The trading lot size of a security

Field.Name: MinTradeVol
Field.Description: The minimum trading volume for a security

Field.Name: MultiLegRptTypeReq
Field.Description: Indicates the method of execution reporting requested by issuer of the order. 0 = Report by mulitleg security only (Do not report legs) 1 = Report by multileg security and by instrument legs belonging to the multileg security. 2 = Report by instrument legs belonging to the multileg security only (Do not report status of multileg security)

Field.Name: LegPositionEffect
Field.Description: PositionEffect for leg of a multileg See PositionEffect (77) field for description

Field.Name: LegCoveredOrUncovered
Field.Description: CoveredOrUncovered for leg of a multileg See CoveredOrUncovered (203) field for description

Field.Name: LegPrice
Field.Description: Price for leg of a multileg See Price (44) field for description

Field.Name: TradSesStatusRejReason
Field.Description: Indicates the reason a Trading Session Status Request was rejected.

Field.Name: TradeRequestID
Field.Description: Trade Capture Report Request ID

Field.Name: TradeRequestType
Field.Description: Type of Trade Capture Report.

Field.Name: PreviouslyReported
Field.Description: Indicates if the trade capture report was previously reported to the counterparty

Field.Name: TradeReportID
Field.Description: Unique identifier of trade capture report

Field.Name: TradeReportRefID
Field.Description: Reference identifier used with CANCEL and REPLACE transaction types.

Field.Name: MatchStatus
Field.Description: The status of this trade with respect to matching or comparison.

Field.Name: MatchType
Field.Description: The point in the matching process at which this trade was matched. Valid values: For NYSE and AMEX: A1 = Exact match on Trade Date, Stock Symbol, Quantity, Price, Trade Type, and Special Trade Indicator plus four badges and execution time (within two-minute window) A2 = Exact match on Trade Date, Stock Symbol, Quantity, Price, Trade Type, and Special Trade Indicator plus four badges A3 = Exact match on Trade Date, Stock Symbol, Quantity, Price, Trade Type, and Special Trade Indicator plus two badges and execution time (within two-minute window) A4 = Exact match on Trade Date, Stock Symbol, Quantity, Price, Trade Type, and Special Trade Indicator plus two badges A5 = Exact match on Trade Date, Stock Symbol, Quantity, Price, Trade Type, and Special Trade Indicator plus execution time (within two-minute window) AQ = Compared records resulting from stamped advisories or specialist accepts/pair-offs S1 to S5 = Summarized Match using A1 to A5 exact match criteria except quantity is summarized M1 = Exact Match on Trade Date, Stock Symbol, Quantity, Price, Trade Type, and Special Trade Indicator minus badges and times M2 = Summarized Match minus badges and times MT = OCS Locked In For NASDAQ: M1 = ACT M1 Match M2 = ACT M2 Match M3 = ACT Accepted Trade M4 = ACT Default Trade M5 = ACT Default After M2 M6 = ACT M6 Match MT = Non-ACT

Field.Name: OddLot
Field.Description: This trade is to be treated as an odd lot Values: Y = treat as odd lot N = treat as round lot If this field is not specified, the default will be "N"

Field.Name: NoClearingInstructions
Field.Description: Number of clearing instructions

Field.Name: ClearingInstruction
Field.Description: Eligibility of this trade for clearing and central counterparty processing values above 4000 are reserved for agreement between parties

Field.Name: TradeInputSource
Field.Description: Type of input device or system from which the trade was entered.

Field.Name: TradeInputDevice
Field.Description: Specific device number, terminal number or station where trade was entered

Field.Name: NoDates
Field.Description: Number of Date fields provided in date range

Field.Name: AccountType
Field.Description: Type of account associated with an order

Field.Name: CustOrderCapacity
Field.Description: Capacity of customer placing the order 1 = Member trading for their own account 2 = Clearing Firm trading for its proprietary account 3 = Member trading for another member 4 = All other Primarily used by futures exchanges to indicate the CTICode (customer type indicator) as required by the US CFTC (Commodity Futures Trading Commission).

Field.Name: ClOrdLinkID
Field.Description: Permits order originators to tie together groups of orders in which trades resulting from orders are associated for a specific purpose, for example the calculation of average execution price for a customer.

Field.Name: MassStatusReqID
Field.Description: Value assigned by issuer of Mass Status Request to uniquely identify the request

Field.Name: MassStatusReqType
Field.Description: Mass Status Request Type

Field.Name: OrigOrdModTime
Field.Description: The most recent (or current) modification TransactTime (tag 60) reported on an Execution Report for the order. The OrigOrdModTime is provided as an optional field on Order Cancel Request and Order Cancel Replace Requests to identify that the state of the order has not changed since the request was issued. This is provided to support markets similar to Eurex and A/C/E.

Field.Name: LegSettlmntTyp
Field.Description: Refer to values for SettlmntTyp[63]

Field.Name: LegFutSettDate
Field.Description: Refer to description for FutSettDate[64]

Field.Name: DayBookingInst
Field.Description: Indicates whether or not automatic booking can occur. 0 = Can trigger booking without reference to the order initiator ("auto") 1 = Speak with order initiator before booking ("speak first")

Field.Name: BookingUnit
Field.Description: Indicates what constitutes a bookable unit. 0 = Each partial execution is a bookable unit 1 = Aggregate partial executions on this order, and book one trade per order 2 = Aggregate executions for this symbol, side, and settlement date

Field.Name: PreallocMethod
Field.Description: Indicates the method of preallocation. 0 = Pro-rata 1 = Do not pro-rata = discuss first

Field.Name: UnderlyingCountryOfIssue
Field.Description: Underlying security’s CountryOfIssue. See CountryOfIssue (470) field for description

Field.Name: UnderlyingStateOrProvinceOfIssue
Field.Description: Underlying security’s StateOrProvinceOfIssue. See StateOrProvinceOfIssue (471) field for description

Field.Name: UnderlyingLocaleOfIssue
Field.Description: Underlying security’s LocaleOfIssue. See LocaleOfIssue (472) field for description

Field.Name: UnderlyingInstrRegistry
Field.Description: Underlying security’s InstrRegistry. See InstrRegistry (543) field for description

Field.Name: LegCountryOfIssue
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual leg security’s CountryOfIssue. See CountryOfIssue (470) field for description

Field.Name: LegStateOrProvinceOfIssue
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual leg security’s StateOrProvinceOfIssue. See StateOrProvinceOfIssue (471) field for description

Field.Name: LegLocaleOfIssue
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual leg security’s LocaleOfIssue. See LocaleOfIssue (472) field for description

Field.Name: LegInstrRegistry
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual leg security’s InstrRegistry. See InstrRegistry (543) field for description

Field.Name: LegSymbol
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s Symbol. See Symbol (55) field for description

Field.Name: LegSymbolSfx
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s SymbolSfx. See SymbolSfx (65) field for description

Field.Name: LegSecurityID
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s SecurityID. See SecurityID (48) field for description

Field.Name: LegSecurityIDSource
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s SecurityIDSource. See SecurityIDSource (22) field for description

Field.Name: NoLegSecurityAltID
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s NoSecurityAltID. See NoSecurityAltID (454) field for description

Field.Name: LegSecurityAltID
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s SecurityAltID. See SecurityAltID (455) field for description

Field.Name: LegSecurityAltIDSource
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s SecurityAltIDSource. See SecurityAltIDSource (456) field for description

Field.Name: LegProduct
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s Product. See Product (460) field for description

Field.Name: LegCFICode
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s CFICode. See CFICode (461) field for description

Field.Name: LegSecurityType
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s SecurityType. See SecurityType (167) field for description

Field.Name: LegMaturityMonthYear
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s MaturityMonthYear. See MaturityMonthYear (200) field for description

Field.Name: LegMaturityDate
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s MaturityDate. See MaturityDate (541) field for description

Field.Name: LegStrikePrice
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s StrikePrice. See StrikePrice (202) field for description

Field.Name: LegOptAttribute
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s OptAttribute. See OptAttribute (206) field for description

Field.Name: LegContractMultiplier
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s ContractMultiplier. See ContractMultiplier (231) field for description

Field.Name: LegCouponRate
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s CouponRate. See CouponRate (223) field for description

Field.Name: LegSecurityExchange
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s SecurityExchange. See SecurityExchange (207) field for description

Field.Name: LegIssuer
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s Issuer. See Issuer (106) field for description

Field.Name: EncodedLegIssuerLen
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s EncodedIssuerLen. See EncodedIssuerLen (348) field for description

Field.Name: EncodedLegIssuer
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s EncodedIssuer. See EncodedIssuer (349) field for description

Field.Name: LegSecurityDesc
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s SecurityDesc. See SecurityDesc (107) field for description

Field.Name: EncodedLegSecurityDescLen
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s EncodedSecurityDescLen. See EncodedSecurityDescLen (350) field for description

Field.Name: EncodedLegSecurityDesc
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s EncodedSecurityDesc. See EncodedSecurityDesc (351) field for description

Field.Name: LegRatioQty
Field.Description: The ratio of quantity for this individual leg relative to the entire multileg security.

Field.Name: LegSide
Field.Description: The side of this individual leg (multileg security). See Side (54) field for description and values

Field.Name: TradingSessionSubID
Field.Description: Optional market assigned sub identifier for a trading session. Usage is determined by market or counterparties. Used by US based futures markets to identify exchange specific execution time bracket codes as required by US market regulations.

Field.Name: AllocType
Field.Description: Describes the specific type or purpose of an Allocation message (i.e. "Buyside Calculated")

Field.Name: NoHops
Field.Description: Number of HopCompID entries in repeating group.

Field.Name: HopCompID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify the third party firm which delivered a specific message either from the firm which originated the message or from another third party (if multiple "hops" are performed). It is recommended that this value be the SenderCompID (49) of the third party. Applicable when messages are communicated/re-distributed via third parties which function as service bureaus or "hubs". Only applicable if OnBehalfOfCompID (115) is being used.

Field.Name: HopSendingTime
Field.Description: Time that HopCompID (628) sent the message. It is recommended that this value be the SendingTime (52) of the message sent by the third party. Applicable when messages are communicated/re-distributed via third parties which function as service bureaus or "hubs". Only applicable if OnBehalfOfCompID (115) is being used.

Field.Name: HopRefID
Field.Description: Reference identifier assigned by HopCompID (628) associated with the message sent. It is recommended that this value be the MsgSeqNum (34) of the message sent by the third party. Applicable when messages are communicated/re-distributed via third parties which function as service bureaus or "hubs". Only applicable if OnBehalfOfCompID (115) is being used.

Field.Name: MidPx
Field.Description: Mid price/rate

Field.Name: BidYield
Field.Description: Bid yield

Field.Name: MidYield
Field.Description: Mid yield

Field.Name: OfferYield
Field.Description: Offer yield

Field.Name: ClearingFeeIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates type of fee being assessed of the customer for trade executions at an exchange. Applicable for futures markets only at this time. Valid Values (source CBOT, CME, NYBOT, and NYMEX): B = CBOE Member C = Non-member and Customer E = Equity Member and Clearing Member F = Full and Associate Member trading for own account and as floor Brokers H = 106.H and 106.J Firms I = GIM, IDEM and COM Membership Interest Holders L = Lessee and 106.F Employees M = All other ownership types 1 = 1st year delegate trading for his own account 2 = 2nd year delegate trading for his own account 3 = 3rd year delegate trading for his own account 4 = 4th year delegate trading for his own account 5 = 5th year delegate trading for his own account 9 = 6th year and beyond delegate trading for his own account

Field.Name: WorkingIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates if the order is currently being worked. Applicable only for OrdStatus = "New". For open outcry markets this indicates that the order is being worked in the crowd. For electronic markets it indicates that the order has transitioned from a contingent order to a market order.

Field.Name: LegLastPx
Field.Description: Execution price assigned to a leg of a multileg instrument. See LastPx (31) field for description and values

Field.Name: PriorityIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates if a Cancel/Replace has caused an order to lose book priority.

Field.Name: PriceImprovement
Field.Description: Amount of price improvement.

Field.Name: Price2
Field.Description: Price of the future part of a F/X swap order. See Price (44) for description.

Field.Name: LastForwardPoints2
Field.Description: F/X forward points of the future part of a F/X swap order added to LastSpotRate. May be a negative value.

Field.Name: BidForwardPoints2
Field.Description: Bid F/X forward points of the future portion of a F/X swap quote added to spot rate. May be a negative value.

Field.Name: OfferForwardPoints2
Field.Description: Offer F/X forward points of the future portion of a F/X swap quote added to spot rate. May be a negative value.

Field.Name: RFQReqID
Field.Description: RFQ Request ID – used to identify an RFQ Request.

Field.Name: MktBidPx
Field.Description: Used to indicate the best bid in a market

Field.Name: MktOfferPx
Field.Description: Used to indicate the best offer in a market

Field.Name: MinBidSize
Field.Description: Used to indicate a minimum quantity for a bid. If this field is used the BidSize field is interpreted as the maximum bid size

Field.Name: MinOfferSize
Field.Description: Used to indicate a minimum quantity for an offer. If this field is used the OfferSize field is interpreted as the maximum offer size.

Field.Name: QuoteStatusReqID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for Quote Status Request.

Field.Name: LegalConfirm
Field.Description: Indicates that this message is to serve as the final and legal confirmation.

Field.Name: UnderlyingLastPx
Field.Description: The calculated or traded price for the underlying instrument that corresponds to a derivative. Used for transactions that include the cash instrument and the derivative.

Field.Name: UnderlyingLastQty
Field.Description: The calculated or traded quantity for the underlying instrument that corresponds to a derivative. Used for transactions that include the cash instrument and the derivative.

Field.Name: LegRefID
Field.Description: Unique indicator for a specific leg.

Field.Name: ContraLegRefID
Field.Description: Unique indicator for a specific leg for the ContraBroker (375).

Field.Name: SettlCurrBidFxRate
Field.Description: Foreign exchange rate used to compute the bid "SettlCurrAmt" from Currency to SettlCurrency

Field.Name: SettlCurrOfferFxRate
Field.Description: Foreign exchange rate used to compute the offer "SettlCurrAmt" from Currency to SettlCurrency

Field.Name: QuoteRequestRejectReason
Field.Description: Reason Quote was rejected:

Field.Name: SideComplianceID
Field.Description: ID within repeating group of sides which is used to represent this transaction for compliance purposes (e.g. OATS reporting).
